  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Front Brake Disc Removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not allow oil or grease to adhere to the sliding surfaces of the brake disc and pads."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The figure shows a vehicle with 12-inch brakes."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Lift Set",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "G000319",
          "label": "Lift Set",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Front wheel removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000659",
          "label": "Front wheel removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Brake caliper and bracket removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "688_3.0_jpn_11035871_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the brake hose clamp bolt (A). Remove the caliper (B) from the knuckle and secure the caliper with a wire or similar."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "When securing the caliper, be very careful not to damage other parts.",
        "Do not suspend the caliper by the brake hose.",
        "Do not forcefully twist the brake hose."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Brake disc removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "688_3.0_jpn_11035872_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the screw (A) and remove the brake disc (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "If the brake disc is stuck due to rust or other reasons and is difficult to remove, tighten the two 8mm bolts (C) evenly to remove it."
        },
        {
          "text": "If the brake disc is stuck due to rust or other reasons and is difficult to remove, tighten the two 8mm bolts (C) evenly to remove it."
        },
        {
          "text": "Do not tilt the brake disc during removal."
        },
        {
          "text": "Do not tilt the brake disc during removal."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure. Clean the mating surfaces of the hub and disc before installing the brake disc."
    }
  ],
